<br />I don't see much difference between my PC which is connected to a CRT screen and the other one who has a LCD. Scrolling text doesn't look very good on the LCD, but there is no noticeable motion blur, and the results of your flickering tests doesn't look like the real hardware at all (no horizontal lines, just flickering yellow/blue).</div>

					
